	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 7th 9:20 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>He's right?! I was about to contradict him, saying that there is no way +1 Int could be of lesser value as +10 Mana in terms of overall mana gain. Sure maybe for a low level twink this would be better. But before I stuck my foot in my mouth, and I went and tried 2 seperate mana calcs, just to see how much more mana +1 Int gives. Here is what I discovered...<br><br>At level 1 an extra +1 Int gives you no extra mana at all. In fact at level 48 +1 Int is only equal to +10 Mana! It's not until level 53 that +1 becomes better than +10 mana, and even then it's only +11 Mana! That means that this item, aside from the negative effects to Charisma, is indeed better than a Spirit Tome and remains so until you reach level 53.<br><br>Never actually bothered to check on this before, but it appears that INT raises are actually rather overrated, since at level 48 +30 Int is only equal to an extra 288 Mana. For my enchanter this means 1 charm and 1 fear spell, not much more...<br><br>Just thought I'd post my thoughts and discoveries on this, flame away...<br>&nbsp;<br>"And from the depths of the Seas of Odus rose a star, one that would shine light for all of Norrath.<br><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76303 target=_new>Onielara Gemcroft</a></td></tr>
