	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>Gratz on the nice item.<br><br>The weight issue for the Harvester isn't a big deal.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's heavy, but you get an STR boost from it.  So, it's effective weight is only 3.  Personally I love the Harvester, because it has the perfect look for a necromancer.  (All I need is to finish the Shadowbound robe quest and I'm the Grim Reaper of the Iksar!  *Grin*)<br><br>The -CHA on this is worse, but you can always put it in a bag.  You have to do that with the Harvester, unless you wanna be poor anyhow.  And finally, you get some nice resists out of this.  (Probably not gonna appreciate them for a while, at L33.)<br><br>What this has going for it in a big way, is that you can put it in primary, or secondary slot.  Which means you can use it and a Harvester if you want.  If your profile is up to date, you're using a black tome in primary, which is maybe a little better than this, but without the resists.<br><br>I'd be inclined to say to hang onto it.  (Even if you're not gonna use it!)  Firstly, there will probably be quite a few of these in circulation just now.  (Relatively speaking.)  So if you did sell it, you'd get a pretty poor price.  Secondly, you may never see one of these again, let alone get a chance to buy one!<br><br>Aside from anything else, if you're short on coins, you can always sell the Harvester, 'cos it's pretty easilly replacable.<br><br>Anyhow, these are my thoughts on it.  If you were on my server, I'd probably tell ya to sell and make you a swift offer, but since you're not...  *Grin*  Of all the Halloween items I have seen, this is one of the nicest.<br><br>AlAaraaf<br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
